{
  "text": "Vasopressin and oxytocin can cause uterine and gastrointestinal smooth muscle contraction. Vasopressin is associated with hypertension, due to its vasoconstrictive properties, as well as uterine contraction pain, nausea and vomiting [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Chest tightness, palpitations, uterine contraction pain, low fever, nausea, vomiting and diarrhea are common adverse effects of oxytocin [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Carboprost tromethamine can cause prostaglandin-like side-effects, such as nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, headaches, hypertension, fever and bronchial asthma [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
